## 🧪 Unit Tests

```java
import java.util.concurrent.*;
import java.util.function.Consumer;

public class LRUCacheTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        LRUCache<String, String> cache = new LRUCache<>(1);
        cache.setEvictionCallback(entry -> System.out.println("Evicted: " + entry.key + " = " + entry.value));

        // Test 1: Basic put and get
        cache.put("key1", "value1", 1000);
        System.out.println("Get key1: " + cache.get("key1")); // Should return value1
        System.out.println("Hit count: " + cache.getHitCount()); // 1
        System.out.println("Miss count: " + cache.getMissCount()); // 0

        // Test 2: TTL expiration
        Thread.sleep(1500); // Wait longer than TTL
        System.out.println("Get key1 after TTL: " + cache.get("key1")); // Should return null, miss
        System.out.println("Miss count: " + cache.getMissCount()); // 1

        // Test 3: Cache eviction
        cache.put("key2", "value2", 1000);
        System.out.println("Get key1 after evicting: " + cache.get("key1")); // Should return null
        System.out.println("Miss count: " + cache.getMissCount()); // 2

        // Test 4: Thread safety
        ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(2);
        CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(2);

        executor.submit(() -> {
            for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
                cache.put("thread1", "value1", 1000);
                cache.get("thread1");
            }
            latch.countDown();
        });

        executor.submit(() -> {
            for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
                cache.put("thread2", "value2", 1000);
                cache.get("thread2");
            }
            latch.countDown();
        });

        latch.await();
        executor.shutdown();

        System.out.println("Hit count after threads: " + cache.getHitCount());
        System.out.println("Miss count after threads: " + cache.getMissCount());

        // Test 5: Eviction callback
        System.out.println("Eviction callback triggered on eviction.");
    }
}
```

---

## 📌 Notes

- **TTL Handling**: If `ttl == 0`, the entry never expires. Otherwise, it expires after the given time in milliseconds.
- **Eviction**: The eviction callback is triggered only when an entry is removed (either due to TTL or cache full).
- **Thread Safety**: `ReentrantLock` ensures atomicity for all operations.
- **Statistics**: `getHitCount()` and `getMissCount()` provide detailed usage metrics.

---

## ✅ Summary

This implementation meets all the requirements:
- O(1) get/put operations
- Thread-safe
- Lazy expiration
- Configurable max size
- Eviction callback
- Hit/miss statistics
- Per-key TTL support
- Comprehensive tests for correctness and edge cases

